0','Sometimes we need our git repositories to NOT track something. We still want that file or directory - but we just want git to pretend it doesn\'t exist.\r\n\r\nWe want git to ignore it.\r\n\r\nThis is not an uncommon request! In fact, it\'s standard practice to group these files / directories together in a specific file which is (perhaps predictably) called the .gitignore.\r\n\r\nHere are two examples of .gitignore files that I will use on WordPress projects - depending on whether or not I am versioning the core files.','These aren\'t the files you are looking for.','','publish','open','open','','git-blind-eye','','','2017-05-30 15:25:19','2017-05-30 15:25:19','',0,'https://redrambles.blog//?p=47671',0,'post','',0),(47672,1,'2016-11-03 15:57:10','2016-11-03 15:57:10','Sometimes we need our git repositories to NOT track something. We still want that file or directory - but we just want git to pretend it doesn\'t exist. \r\n\r\nWe want git to ignore it.\r\n\r\nThis is not an uncommon request! In fact, it\'s standard practice to group these files / directories together in a specific file which is (perhaps predictably) called the .gitignore.\r\n\r\nHere are two examples of .gitignore files that I will use on WordPress projects - depending on whether or not I am versioning the core files.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"git-core\">.gitignore file with files versioned \r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/redrambles/257f953bc3873caea3ddc7f3bd75c27a.js\"></script>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"git-no-core\">.gitignore file without files versioned \r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/redrambles/36a138f5609440ebcbb73bba3e6a0f1a.js\"></script>\r\n</div>','Lalalalala - I can\'t heeeaaaar youuuuuu','','inherit','closed','closed','','47671-revision-v1','','','2016-11-03 15:57:10','2016-11-03 15:57:10','',47671,'https://redrambles.blog//47671-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(47673,1,'2016-11-08 15:36:17','2016-11-08 15:36:17','Sometimes we need our git repositories to NOT track