ng walks with my dogs.\n\n</div>','Hi, I\'m Ann. </br> I love building websites.','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-v1','','','2017-07-11 16:54:37','2017-07-11 16:54:37','',4,'https://redrambles.blog//4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(47876,1,'2017-07-11 16:55:30','2017-07-11 16:55:30','<div>\r\n\r\n<p>I’m a student of all things web development and hack away at various code projects with the passion of a zealot. I\'m also a mom of a small pack of minions who will one day do my bidding. (For now, I\'m working on our family grocery shopping time NOT shaving years off of my life. <a href=\"https://redrambles.blog//git-blind-eye/\" target=\"_blank\">I also love git!</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>During my off-parent duties, when I’m not crafting code (which in fairness - is most of the time), I like to sing, play the mandolin, curl up with a good sci-fi/fantasy book or take long walks with my dogs.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>','Hi, I\'m Ann. </br> I love building websites.','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-v1','','','2017-07-11 16:55:30','2017-07-11 16:55:30','',4,'https://redrambles.blog//4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(47878,1,'2017-08-22 15:33:00','2017-08-22 15:33:00','You have a local project, you\'ve put it under version control and now you want to use Git\'s awesome powers to push all of your files over to your live site - because SFTP blows. Right?! Dreamhost say that they support Git, so I figured - righto - let\'s get this show on the road!\r\n\r\nEhhhhhh - This is where things got murky - at least for me. The documentation I unearthed was incomplete at best. Though Git <strong>is</strong> already installed on my Dreamhost server, that was pretty much the end of git support, at least in so far as I found. (sad emoji)\r\n\r\nSo! I decided to do what I always do in these situations: pour myself a glass of wine, put on some good tunes, crack open my terminal and hack at things until I get the result I\'m after. Once I was successful (yay!) - I put toget